This paper is about using attention-based neural networks to improve the recognition of implicit discourse relations. The paper focuses on natural language processing and machine learning techniques, which are typically covered in the cs.CL (Computation and Language) sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves the use of neural networks, which are commonly studied in the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-categories. The paper also involves the use of semantic memory, which is studied in the cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) sub-category. Finally, the paper involves information retrieval techniques, which are studied in the cs.IR (Information Retrieval) sub-category.
